"{\"uid\": \"nytimes.com-athletic-5429739-2024-04-20-olympics-ai-bach-vonn-paris\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Olympics Follow The Athletic'sOlympicscoveragehere.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 54, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympics\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 8}, {\"ngram\": \"The Athletic'sOlympicscoveragehere\", \"from\": 16, \"to\": 50}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The video flickers onto three big screens, grainy footage showing International Olympic Committee (IOC) president Thomas Bach, then a callow 22-year-old, winning his gold medal at the 1976 MontrealOlympics.\", \"from\": 56, \"to\": 262, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 122, \"end\": 159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 122, \"end\": 159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 170, \"end\": 181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The video\", \"from\": 56, \"to\": 65}, {\"ngram\": \"three big screens\", \"from\": 80, \"to\": 97}, {\"ngram\": \"his gold medal\", \"from\": 218, \"to\": 232}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1976 MontrealOlympics\", \"from\": 236, \"to\": 261}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Thanks for showing that I have not changed at all,\\\" quips the German, now 70, and the most powerful figure at the IOC after an 11-year tenure which shows no signs of stopping.\", \"from\": 264, \"to\": 440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 327, \"end\": 333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.9999960006005435, \"rank\": 3.0263886044569663e-06, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}, {\"begin\": 379, \"end\": 382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.089507901616471e-47, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Thanks\", \"from\": 265, \"to\": 271}, {\"ngram\": \"the most powerful figure\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 371}, {\"ngram\": \"an 11-year tenure\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 406}, {\"ngram\": \"no signs\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 427}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The reality, and the reason why he is speaking, is that theOlympicGames themselvesarechanging.\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 536, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The reality\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 453}, {\"ngram\": \"the reason\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 469}, {\"ngram\": \"that theOlympicGames themselvesarechanging\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 535}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement Earlier this week, it was announced that World Athletics would pay $50,000 (\\u00a340,353) for each track and field gold medal in Paris this summer - a first in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 724, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 594, \"end\": 609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3735694450626718e-24, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 677, \"end\": 682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7546070776395576e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"each track and field gold medal\", \"from\": 641, \"to\": 672}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic history\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 722}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This Games will see breakdancing introduced while surfing, making its second appearance, will take place almost 10,000 miles away from the host city in Tahiti.\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.62902139759057e-12, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This Games\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 735}, {\"ngram\": \"its second appearance\", \"from\": 791, \"to\": 812}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 829}, {\"ngram\": \"the host city\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 873}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And now at a launch event at London's Olympic Velodrome, with Champagne handed out from 1pm and a table devoted solely to French pastries, Bach is explaining why theOlympicmovement, known for its traditionalism and amateur values, is embracing artificial intelligence (AI).\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 1161, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 917, \"end\": 923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1065277486409635e-16, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 950, \"end\": 959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champagne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.489243184379985e-21, \"text\": \"Champagne\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champagne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champagne\"}, {\"begin\": 1010, \"end\": 1016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999445771788863, \"rank\": 3.300840916942885e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1027, \"end\": 1031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7992047397633535e-23, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a launch event\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 913}, {\"ngram\": \"theOlympicmovement\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1068}, {\"ngram\": \"its traditionalism\", \"from\": 1080, \"to\": 1098}, {\"ngram\": \"amateur values\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1117}, {\"ngram\": \"artificial intelligence\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1155}, {\"ngram\": \"AI\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1159}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are at a crossroads of change,\\\" he tells the room.\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1217, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a crossroads\", \"from\": 1174, \"to\": 1186}, {\"ngram\": \"change\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1196}, {\"ngram\": \"the room\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1216}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We can only be the leader of change if you take a holistic approach.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1287, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the leader\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1244}, {\"ngram\": \"change\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1254}, {\"ngram\": \"a holistic approach\", \"from\": 1267, \"to\": 1286}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are representing the first holistic approach - the Olympic AI Agenda.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first holistic approach\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1335}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic AI Agenda\", \"from\": 1338, \"to\": 1359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a conceptual and practical approach.\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1403, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a conceptual and practical approach\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1402}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It defines our ambition and our guiding principles, embracing the full potential of AI.\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1488, \"end\": 1490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.816253114838095e-17, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our ambition\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1427}, {\"ngram\": \"our guiding principles\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1454}, {\"ngram\": \"the full potential\", \"from\": 1466, \"to\": 1484}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But at the centre of the agenda is the human.\", \"from\": 1492, \"to\": 1537, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the centre\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1509}, {\"ngram\": \"the agenda\", \"from\": 1513, \"to\": 1523}, {\"ngram\": \"the human\", \"from\": 1527, \"to\": 1536}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The athlete.\\\"\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The athlete\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1549}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike other areas, he theorises, sport does not face an existential question - \\\"the 100m will always have to be run by an athlete\\\" - meaning they are free, as administrators, to develop the technology to support participants.\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1779, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other areas\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1571}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"an existential question\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1630}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100m\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1642}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 1673, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"administrators\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1727}, {\"ngram\": \"the technology\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1754}, {\"ngram\": \"participants\", \"from\": 1766, \"to\": 1778}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Embrace the change,\\\" is the final line of his opening address, \\\"but retain Olympic values.\\\"\", \"from\": 1780, \"to\": 1872, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the change\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1799}, {\"ngram\": \"the final line\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1819}, {\"ngram\": \"his opening address\", \"from\": 1823, \"to\": 1842}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic values\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 1870}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As his words die away to a smattering of applause, alpine skier Lindsey Vonn, one of the United States' most famous Winter Olympians, limps onto the stage.\", \"from\": 1874, \"to\": 2029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1938, \"end\": 1950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Vonn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lindsey Vonn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4270517\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Vonn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Vonn\"}, {\"begin\": 1963, \"end\": 1976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9900029204535943, \"rank\": 0.010098030358753913, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his words\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1886}, {\"ngram\": \"a smattering\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1911}, {\"ngram\": \"applause\", \"from\": 1915, \"to\": 1923}, {\"ngram\": \"the stage\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2028}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her latest knee surgery, suitably, has been performed by a robot.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2095, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her latest knee surgery\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2053}, {\"ngram\": \"a robot\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2094}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has been invited to talk about AI's role in talent identification.\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2132, \"end\": 2134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.816253114838095e-17, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"talent identification\", \"from\": 2145, \"to\": 2166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite being born in the relative flatness of Minnesota, hers was a skiing family and her talent was recognised at an early age.\", \"from\": 2168, \"to\": 2297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2215, \"end\": 2224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9893104037721878, \"rank\": 0.01080509827999476, \"text\": \"Minnesota\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the relative flatness\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2211}, {\"ngram\": \"a skiing family\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2250}, {\"ngram\": \"her talent\", \"from\": 2255, \"to\": 2265}, {\"ngram\": \"an early age\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2296}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She benefited from access to further support and coaching.\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2356, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"access\", \"from\": 2317, \"to\": 2323}, {\"ngram\": \"further support\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2342}, {\"ngram\": \"coaching\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2355}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That, she openly admits, was fortunate.\", \"from\": 2357, \"to\": 2396, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, they hope to use AI to test children in developing nations to find sports for those with raw but transferable athletic abilities.\", \"from\": 2397, \"to\": 2531, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2419, \"end\": 2421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.816253114838095e-17, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"children\", \"from\": 2430, \"to\": 2438}, {\"ngram\": \"nations\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2460}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 2469, \"to\": 2475}, {\"ngram\": \"raw but transferable athletic abilities\", \"from\": 2491, \"to\": 2530}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement Last year, the IOC visited Senegal carrying hardware equipment for both physical and cognitive tests.\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2563, \"end\": 2566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.089507901616471e-47, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2575, \"end\": 2582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senegal\", \"score\": 0.9999999983938324, \"rank\": 1.6062922627723287e-09, \"text\": \"Senegal\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senegal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senegal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Advertisement\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2546}, {\"ngram\": \"hardware equipment\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2609}, {\"ngram\": \"both physical and cognitive tests\", \"from\": 2614, \"to\": 2647}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Outside the velodrome, suppliers Intel have brought a larger-scale, futuristic version.\", \"from\": 2650, \"to\": 2737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2683, \"end\": 2688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intel\", \"score\": 0.9999999999254214, \"rank\": 7.49679904686609e-11, \"text\": \"Intel\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Intel\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the velodrome\", \"from\": 2658, \"to\": 2671}, {\"ngram\": \"a larger-scale, futuristic version\", \"from\": 2702, \"to\": 2736}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Senegal, the team visited six villages over six days, testing 1,000 children of whom 40 were deemed to have \\\"superb\\\" ability - the raw potential to perhaps compete in theOlympics.\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2741, \"end\": 2748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senegal\", \"score\": 0.9999999983938324, \"rank\": 1.6062922627723287e-09, \"text\": \"Senegal\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senegal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senegal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2758}, {\"ngram\": \"six villages\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 2779}, {\"ngram\": \"six days\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2793}, {\"ngram\": \"1,000 children\", \"from\": 2803, \"to\": 2817}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"superb\\\" ability\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 2865}, {\"ngram\": \"the raw potential\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 2885}, {\"ngram\": \"theOlympics\", \"from\": 2908, \"to\": 2919}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One child recorded numbers in several tests comparable to those in the national sprint team.\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 3014, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One child\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 2931}, {\"ngram\": \"numbers\", \"from\": 2941, \"to\": 2948}, {\"ngram\": \"several tests\", \"from\": 2952, \"to\": 2965}, {\"ngram\": \"the national sprint team\", \"from\": 2989, \"to\": 3013}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think it's going to be a huge opportunity,\\\" says Vonn.\", \"from\": 3016, \"to\": 3073, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a huge opportunity\", \"from\": 3042, \"to\": 3060}, {\"ngram\": \"Vonn\", \"from\": 3068, \"to\": 3072}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So many kids quit sports early because they do not know they are talented, or their coaches do not believe it.\", \"from\": 3074, \"to\": 3185, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"So many kids\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3087}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 3093, \"to\": 3099}, {\"ngram\": \"their coaches\", \"from\": 3153, \"to\": 3166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will prove these kids can be something.\\\"\", \"from\": 3186, \"to\": 3231, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these kids\", \"from\": 3202, \"to\": 3212}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 3220, \"to\": 3229}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It would prove to my Dad that I'd have been an amazing tennis player,\\\" she adds, joking.\", \"from\": 3233, \"to\": 3322, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3255, \"end\": 3258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revenge\", \"score\": 0.990301095112806, \"rank\": 0.009793894942772727, \"text\": \"Dad\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revenge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Revenge\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an amazing tennis player\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3302}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I actually do not like the cold.\", \"from\": 3323, \"to\": 3356, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the cold\", \"from\": 3347, \"to\": 3355}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am very jealous.\\\"\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3376, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While intending to improve accessibility, with capacity currently limited, one of the key questions the IOC are wrestling with is how to achieve equality of accessibility between interested federations.\", \"from\": 3378, \"to\": 3580, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3482, \"end\": 3485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.089507901616471e-47, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"accessibility\", \"from\": 3405, \"to\": 3418}, {\"ngram\": \"capacity\", \"from\": 3425, \"to\": 3433}, {\"ngram\": \"the key questions\", \"from\": 3460, \"to\": 3477}, {\"ngram\": \"equality\", \"from\": 3523, \"to\": 3531}, {\"ngram\": \"accessibility\", \"from\": 3535, \"to\": 3548}, {\"ngram\": \"interested federations\", \"from\": 3557, \"to\": 3579}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"All the solutions which will be developed will be made available for everyone,\\\" Christophe Dubi, executive director of Paris 2024, tellsThe Athletic.\", \"from\": 3582, \"to\": 3732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3702, \"end\": 3712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9699250649428554e-36, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"All the solutions\", \"from\": 3583, \"to\": 3600}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 3652, \"to\": 3660}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\" Christophe Dubi\", \"from\": 3661, \"to\": 3678}, {\"ngram\": \"executive director\", \"from\": 3680, \"to\": 3698}, {\"ngram\": \"tellsThe Athletic\", \"from\": 3714, \"to\": 3731}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That sense of solidarity is very important.\", \"from\": 3733, \"to\": 3777, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That sense\", \"from\": 3734, \"to\": 3744}, {\"ngram\": \"solidarity\", \"from\": 3748, \"to\": 3758}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can not create discrimination through technology.\\\"\", \"from\": 3778, \"to\": 3832, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"discrimination\", \"from\": 3797, \"to\": 3811}, {\"ngram\": \"technology\", \"from\": 3820, \"to\": 3830}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The same focus on accessibility is pushed throughout a presentation on athlete performance, led by two-time Olympic triathlon gold medalist Alistair Brownlee and shooter James Huckle, who began building ballistics models using AI while training for the 2012 Games.\", \"from\": 3834, \"to\": 4098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3974, \"end\": 3991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alistair Brownlee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alistair_Brownlee\"}, {\"begin\": 4004, \"end\": 4016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Huckle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"James Huckle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Huckle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Huckle\"}, {\"begin\": 4061, \"end\": 4063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.816253114838095e-17, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The same focus\", \"from\": 3834, \"to\": 3848}, {\"ngram\": \"accessibility\", \"from\": 3852, \"to\": 3865}, {\"ngram\": \"a presentation\", \"from\": 3887, \"to\": 3901}, {\"ngram\": \"athlete performance\", \"from\": 3905, \"to\": 3924}, {\"ngram\": \"ballistics models\", \"from\": 4037, \"to\": 4054}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2012 Games\", \"from\": 4083, \"to\": 4097}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Using ChatGPT, the most powerful widely available AI tool, both discussed the possibility of athletes gaining cheap access to sports psychology or allowing ChatGPT to perform the data analysis, taking the time-consuming process out of the hands of the coach who can then focus on the human element.\", \"from\": 4100, \"to\": 4398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4150, \"end\": 4152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.816253114838095e-17, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ChatGPT\", \"from\": 4106, \"to\": 4113}, {\"ngram\": \"the possibility\", \"from\": 4174, \"to\": 4189}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 4193, \"to\": 4201}, {\"ngram\": \"cheap access\", \"from\": 4210, \"to\": 4222}, {\"ngram\": \"sports psychology\", \"from\": 4226, \"to\": 4243}, {\"ngram\": \"ChatGPT\", \"from\": 4256, \"to\": 4263}, {\"ngram\": \"the data analysis\", \"from\": 4275, \"to\": 4292}, {\"ngram\": \"the time-consuming process\", \"from\": 4301, \"to\": 4327}, {\"ngram\": \"the hands\", \"from\": 4335, \"to\": 4344}, {\"ngram\": \"the coach\", \"from\": 4348, \"to\": 4357}, {\"ngram\": \"the human element\", \"from\": 4380, \"to\": 4397}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Could this also, one day, be used to help anti-doping efforts?\", \"from\": 4399, \"to\": 4461, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anti-doping efforts\", \"from\": 4441, \"to\": 4460}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement \\\"If you consider that AI is able to deal with a greater number (of cases) and analyse them much, much quicker than we ever could, there is no reason why anti-doping would not benefit,\\\" says Dubi.\", \"from\": 4463, \"to\": 4673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4500, \"end\": 4502, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.816253114838095e-17, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a greater number\", \"from\": 4523, \"to\": 4539}, {\"ngram\": \"cases\", \"from\": 4544, \"to\": 4549}, {\"ngram\": \"no reason\", \"from\": 4616, \"to\": 4625}, {\"ngram\": \"Dubi\", \"from\": 4667, \"to\": 4671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am certain that WADA (World Anti-Doping Agency) is thinking about bringing in AI.\\\"\", \"from\": 4674, \"to\": 4759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4699, \"end\": 4723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Anti-Doping Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 4755, \"end\": 4757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.816253114838095e-17, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WADA\", \"from\": 4693, \"to\": 4697}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the top end of athlete performance, there is also technology in development which could revolutionise training methodology, particularly in one-vs-one sport.\", \"from\": 4761, \"to\": 4921, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the top end\", \"from\": 4764, \"to\": 4775}, {\"ngram\": \"athlete performance\", \"from\": 4779, \"to\": 4798}, {\"ngram\": \"technology\", \"from\": 4814, \"to\": 4824}, {\"ngram\": \"development\", \"from\": 4828, \"to\": 4839}, {\"ngram\": \"training methodology\", \"from\": 4866, \"to\": 4886}, {\"ngram\": \"one-vs-one sport\", \"from\": 4904, \"to\": 4920}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, using data provided by the Alibaba Cloud, the IOC have constructed table tennis technology which mimics the style of two-time gold medallist Xu Xin.\", \"from\": 4922, \"to\": 5083, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4981, \"end\": 4984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.089507901616471e-47, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 5076, \"end\": 5082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xu_Xin_(table_tennis)\", \"score\": 0.9922602644025643, \"rank\": 0.0042305658381808576, \"text\": \"Xu Xin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13382519\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xu_Xin_(table_tennis)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xu_Xin_(table_tennis)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 4926, \"to\": 4933}, {\"ngram\": \"data\", \"from\": 4941, \"to\": 4945}, {\"ngram\": \"the Alibaba Cloud\", \"from\": 4958, \"to\": 4975}, {\"ngram\": \"table tennis technology\", \"from\": 5002, \"to\": 5025}, {\"ngram\": \"the style\", \"from\": 5039, \"to\": 5048}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Players can play against themselves - as Xin already has - or, more intriguingly, one day face potential opponents.\", \"from\": 5085, \"to\": 5200, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Players\", \"from\": 5085, \"to\": 5092}, {\"ngram\": \"Xin\", \"from\": 5126, \"to\": 5129}, {\"ngram\": \"one day\", \"from\": 5167, \"to\": 5174}, {\"ngram\": \"potential opponents\", \"from\": 5180, \"to\": 5199}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There are going to be risks associated with this,\\\" says Huckle, sounding a note of warning.\", \"from\": 5202, \"to\": 5294, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"risks\", \"from\": 5225, \"to\": 5230}, {\"ngram\": \"Huckle\", \"from\": 5259, \"to\": 5265}, {\"ngram\": \"a note\", \"from\": 5276, \"to\": 5282}, {\"ngram\": \"warning\", \"from\": 5286, \"to\": 5293}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But it's going to be powered by the human and led by that development.\", \"from\": 5295, \"to\": 5366, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the human\", \"from\": 5328, \"to\": 5337}, {\"ngram\": \"that development\", \"from\": 5349, \"to\": 5365}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In sport, there is not too much (to worry about), but we have to be aware of the data which these models have been trained on.\\\"\", \"from\": 5367, \"to\": 5494, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 5370, \"to\": 5375}, {\"ngram\": \"the data\", \"from\": 5444, \"to\": 5452}, {\"ngram\": \"these models\", \"from\": 5459, \"to\": 5471}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nadia Comaneci is on stage.\", \"from\": 5496, \"to\": 5523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5496, \"end\": 5510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\", \"score\": 0.9999999839874364, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nadia Comaneci\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"stage\", \"from\": 5517, \"to\": 5522}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Romanian gymnast is an iconic figure after scoring the first-ever perfect 10.0 at the 1976 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 5524, \"to\": 5633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5528, \"end\": 5536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romanian_language\", \"score\": 0.9999998515813896, \"rank\": 1.374010529650364e-07, \"text\": \"Romanian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romanian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romanian_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an iconic figure\", \"from\": 5548, \"to\": 5564}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1976 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 5610, \"to\": 5632}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Would you have been better with this technology?\\\"\", \"from\": 5635, \"to\": 5685, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this technology\", \"from\": 5668, \"to\": 5683}]}, {\"sentence\": \"she is asked.\", \"from\": 5686, \"to\": 5699, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Probably not,\\\" comes the instant reply.\", \"from\": 5701, \"to\": 5741, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the instant reply\", \"from\": 5723, \"to\": 5740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With current technology, would she have been given that perfect 10.0?\", \"from\": 5743, \"to\": 5812, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"current technology\", \"from\": 5748, \"to\": 5766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Comaneci is there to discuss the use of AI in judging - probably the most immediately controversial aspect of the agenda.\", \"from\": 5814, \"to\": 5935, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5854, \"end\": 5856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.816253114838095e-17, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Comaneci\", \"from\": 5814, \"to\": 5822}, {\"ngram\": \"the use\", \"from\": 5843, \"to\": 5850}, {\"ngram\": \"judging\", \"from\": 5860, \"to\": 5867}, {\"ngram\": \"probably the most immediately controversial aspect\", \"from\": 5870, \"to\": 5920}, {\"ngram\": \"the agenda\", \"from\": 5924, \"to\": 5934}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Simone Biles, returning to theOlympicsas the most-decorated gymnast of all time, might need a machine's approval if she is to increase her lead.\", \"from\": 5936, \"to\": 6080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5936, \"end\": 5948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theOlympicsas\", \"from\": 5963, \"to\": 5976}, {\"ngram\": \"the most-decorated gymnast\", \"from\": 5977, \"to\": 6003}, {\"ngram\": \"all time\", \"from\": 6007, \"to\": 6015}, {\"ngram\": \"a machine's approval\", \"from\": 6028, \"to\": 6048}, {\"ngram\": \"her lead\", \"from\": 6071, \"to\": 6079}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC will not yet reveal exactly how much AI technology they will use during the Games, but the central message is that it is there to augment the judging, rather than replace it.\", \"from\": 6082, \"to\": 6264, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6086, \"end\": 6089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.089507901616471e-47, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"exactly how much AI technology\", \"from\": 6110, \"to\": 6140}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 6162, \"to\": 6171}, {\"ngram\": \"the central message\", \"from\": 6177, \"to\": 6196}, {\"ngram\": \"the judging\", \"from\": 6228, \"to\": 6239}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Similar language, and aims, were used around the introduction of video assistant referees in soccer.\", \"from\": 6265, \"to\": 6365, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Similar language\", \"from\": 6265, \"to\": 6281}, {\"ngram\": \"aims\", \"from\": 6287, \"to\": 6291}, {\"ngram\": \"the introduction\", \"from\": 6310, \"to\": 6326}, {\"ngram\": \"video assistant referees\", \"from\": 6330, \"to\": 6354}, {\"ngram\": \"soccer\", \"from\": 6358, \"to\": 6364}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement For example, in trampolining or gymnastics where deductions are given for landing outside the zone, potential indiscretions can be difficult to spot.\", \"from\": 6367, \"to\": 6531, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 6385, \"to\": 6392}, {\"ngram\": \"trampolining\", \"from\": 6397, \"to\": 6409}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnastics\", \"from\": 6413, \"to\": 6423}, {\"ngram\": \"deductions\", \"from\": 6430, \"to\": 6440}, {\"ngram\": \"the zone\", \"from\": 6471, \"to\": 6479}, {\"ngram\": \"potential indiscretions\", \"from\": 6481, \"to\": 6504}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Diving, focused on entry angles, is another relevant sport.\", \"from\": 6532, \"to\": 6591, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Diving\", \"from\": 6532, \"to\": 6538}, {\"ngram\": \"entry angles\", \"from\": 6551, \"to\": 6563}, {\"ngram\": \"another relevant sport\", \"from\": 6568, \"to\": 6590}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With real-time data, these 'objective' points can be instantly reviewed, in theory allowing the judges to focus on more nuanced areas.\", \"from\": 6592, \"to\": 6726, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"real-time data\", \"from\": 6597, \"to\": 6611}, {\"ngram\": \"these 'objective' points\", \"from\": 6613, \"to\": 6637}, {\"ngram\": \"theory\", \"from\": 6668, \"to\": 6674}, {\"ngram\": \"the judges\", \"from\": 6684, \"to\": 6694}, {\"ngram\": \"more nuanced areas\", \"from\": 6707, \"to\": 6725}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With proper modelling, we can have detailed information of the entire performance of an athlete: their rotation, speed, angles, everything that is crucial for judging,\\\" says Alain Zobrist, the CEO of Swiss Timing, part of Omega, the Games' official timekeeper.\", \"from\": 6728, \"to\": 6989, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6929, \"end\": 6934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9999992304722815, \"rank\": 7.695287163151065e-07, \"text\": \"Swiss\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 6951, \"end\": 6956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omega\", \"score\": 0.9348023497412025, \"rank\": 0.06974451154605374, \"text\": \"Omega\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omega\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omega\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"proper modelling\", \"from\": 6734, \"to\": 6750}, {\"ngram\": \"detailed information\", \"from\": 6764, \"to\": 6784}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire performance\", \"from\": 6788, \"to\": 6810}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 6814, \"to\": 6824}, {\"ngram\": \"their rotation\", \"from\": 6826, \"to\": 6840}, {\"ngram\": \"speed\", \"from\": 6842, \"to\": 6847}, {\"ngram\": \"angles\", \"from\": 6849, \"to\": 6855}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 6857, \"to\": 6867}, {\"ngram\": \"judging\", \"from\": 6888, \"to\": 6895}, {\"ngram\": \"Alain Zobrist\", \"from\": 6903, \"to\": 6916}, {\"ngram\": \"the CEO\", \"from\": 6918, \"to\": 6925}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 6943, \"to\": 6947}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games' official timekeeper\", \"from\": 6958, \"to\": 6988}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We can analyse it in sequencing and do all of that in real-time.\", \"from\": 6990, \"to\": 7055, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"real-time\", \"from\": 7045, \"to\": 7054}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It shows the opportunities and the information which we can share with judges, but also to start understanding these performances much better.\\\"\", \"from\": 7057, \"to\": 7201, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the opportunities\", \"from\": 7067, \"to\": 7084}, {\"ngram\": \"the information\", \"from\": 7089, \"to\": 7104}, {\"ngram\": \"judges\", \"from\": 7129, \"to\": 7135}, {\"ngram\": \"these performances\", \"from\": 7169, \"to\": 7187}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When I was competing, we used to have to do compulsory exercises.\", \"from\": 7203, \"to\": 7269, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"compulsory exercises\", \"from\": 7248, \"to\": 7268}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone had to do the same skill - it would have helped then,\\\" agrees Comaneci.\", \"from\": 7270, \"to\": 7350, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Everyone\", \"from\": 7270, \"to\": 7278}, {\"ngram\": \"the same skill\", \"from\": 7289, \"to\": 7303}, {\"ngram\": \"Comaneci\", \"from\": 7341, \"to\": 7349}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It should not eliminate the judging, but it will help a lot.\", \"from\": 7351, \"to\": 7412, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the judging\", \"from\": 7376, \"to\": 7387}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 7406, \"to\": 7411}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you do it the right way, you can work out the shoulder locations, whether there should be bonus points\\u2026 it can help identify details.\\\"\", \"from\": 7413, \"to\": 7550, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the shoulder locations\", \"from\": 7458, \"to\": 7480}, {\"ngram\": \"bonus points\", \"from\": 7506, \"to\": 7518}, {\"ngram\": \"details\", \"from\": 7541, \"to\": 7548}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She does, however, point out one drawback: that if the machine is fed one routine to judge, athletes are allowed to enter competitions with a 'Plan B' in the back of their minds, which they may opt to switch to mid-performance.\", \"from\": 7552, \"to\": 7779, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one drawback\", \"from\": 7581, \"to\": 7593}, {\"ngram\": \"the machine\", \"from\": 7603, \"to\": 7614}, {\"ngram\": \"one routine\", \"from\": 7622, \"to\": 7633}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 7644, \"to\": 7652}, {\"ngram\": \"competitions\", \"from\": 7674, \"to\": 7686}, {\"ngram\": \"a 'Plan B\", \"from\": 7692, \"to\": 7701}, {\"ngram\": \"the back\", \"from\": 7706, \"to\": 7714}, {\"ngram\": \"their minds\", \"from\": 7718, \"to\": 7729}, {\"ngram\": \"mid\", \"from\": 7763, \"to\": 7766}, {\"ngram\": \"performance\", \"from\": 7767, \"to\": 7778}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not that legislating for that seems an insurmountable obstacle.\", \"from\": 7780, \"to\": 7843, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an insurmountable obstacle\", \"from\": 7816, \"to\": 7842}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If judging is the area with the most immediate scope for controversy, there are other more subtle issues about which critics are concerned.\", \"from\": 7845, \"to\": 7984, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"judging\", \"from\": 7848, \"to\": 7855}, {\"ngram\": \"the area\", \"from\": 7859, \"to\": 7867}, {\"ngram\": \"the most immediate scope\", \"from\": 7873, \"to\": 7897}, {\"ngram\": \"controversy\", \"from\": 7902, \"to\": 7913}, {\"ngram\": \"other more subtle issues\", \"from\": 7925, \"to\": 7949}, {\"ngram\": \"critics\", \"from\": 7962, \"to\": 7969}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite an in-depth discussion of safeguarding and security, there was no mention of the Games' controversial surveillance programme which will utilise AI technology.\", \"from\": 7986, \"to\": 8152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8138, \"end\": 8140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.816253114838095e-17, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an in-depth discussion\", \"from\": 7994, \"to\": 8016}, {\"ngram\": \"safeguarding\", \"from\": 8020, \"to\": 8032}, {\"ngram\": \"security\", \"from\": 8037, \"to\": 8045}, {\"ngram\": \"no mention\", \"from\": 8057, \"to\": 8067}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games' controversial surveillance programme\", \"from\": 8071, \"to\": 8118}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Approved ahead of the sum